com.audiofetch.afaudiolib.bll.colleagues

Class WifiController

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.audiofetch.afaudiolib.bll.colleagues.base.ControllerBase
      • com.audiofetch.afaudiolib.bll.colleagues.WifiController

  • public class WifiController
extends ControllerBase
    Wraps Wifi logic for use in SDK Posts events via EventBus, which can be @Subcribe'd to using these event classes:
    See Also:
    - Posts a WifiEvent when dis/connected, or enabled/disabled.

        public WifiController setStatusChangedListener(com.audiofetch.afaudiolib.bll.colleagues.WifiController.OnWifiStatusChangeListener l)
        Sets the WifiController.OnWifiStatusChangeListener for this object. This listener will be called prior to the bus event WifiStatusEvent. It will be fired when the Wifi status has changed state in mWifiReceiver, or whenever the user turns off/on wifi or they gain/lose a signal.
